* Iron Raptor almost seemed to feel naked and vulnerable as Prowl had let go of her and began towards the CR chambers, since their first...contact it just didn't feel right sometimes when he went away. But life went on and it just so happened that both of them were part of it, being apart was just a natural phase in order for it to continue.
She then took in a deep breath and let it out slowly, looking absentmindedly at the Ark's armor but not really noticing that it was there. But then she began to follow up in Prowl's footsteps and make her own way towards the Maximal ship, his last comment about her weight hanging in the air. She growled softly at it as she came up beside Prowl, but a small smile began to form at the corners of her lips that betrayed that there was no intended threat behind it.
Iron Raptor then bumped the side of Prowl's hips gently with her own before she passed him a bit, her optics mockingly narrowed.*

" Weight's one thing...but at least I don't have to worry about pin-feathers."

* She said this with a calm and collected voice as they both continued towards the Ark the touch of sarcasm hanging in the air.*
